<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="905" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d905">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 855.48/468</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the Commission for Relief in
                                Belgium</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hoover</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">New York, N. Y.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 24, 1917</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5.30 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>We this morning received word from London that British Government had
                            issued safe-conduct to ships around northern route, and we anticipate
                            that master, steamer <hi rend="italic">Olaf Kyrre</hi> will receive his
                            pass immediately. We have requested British Ambassador, <persName corresp="#p_WHL1">Washington</persName> to expedite matter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HH1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Herbert Hoover</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>